      "writtenOn": "2020-01-31T00:42:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For comparison sake I uploaded a draft that has implementations for gdb, gdb/mi, and readelf. The latter 2 are arguably incomplete.  The gdb/mi version doesn\u0027t try to handle the various optional data that the grammar allows in the output (though most seems pertinent for getting additional feedback while running an app [which this doesn\u0027t do]).  For readelf it handles 32-bit vs. 64-bit but currently only handles 1 kind of endian (arm is configurable and apparently CrOS uses the same endian as Intel arch).\n\nAs for qemu, I think that\u0027d bring additional sdk/toolchain dependencies to run, and probably also require per-arch VMs to run the app.",
      "parentUuid": "f17e7c82_91539a7c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 39,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 57,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "9307c3eeaad1b53c92105afa846071f2349b9be7",
